<refnamediv><indexterm><primary sortas="create-http-lb">create-http-lb &mdash;
creates a load balancer using a load balancer configuration</primary></indexterm>
<indexterm><primary sortas="creates a load balancer using a load balancer configuration">
creates a load balancer using a load balancer configuration &mdash; create-http-lb 
</primary></indexterm><refname>create-http-lb </refname><refpurpose>creates
a load balancer using a load balancer configuration</refpurpose></refnamediv>
<refsynopsisdiv><title>&synp-tt;</title>
<cmdsynopsis><command>create-http-lb</command>&synopsis-common;
<arg choice="plain">&Dash;&Dash;config <replaceable>lb_config_name</replaceable></arg>
<arg>&Dash;&Dash;autoapplyenabled=<replaceable>false</replaceable></arg><arg
choice="plain">&Dash;&Dash;devicehost <replaceable>device_host_or_IP_address
</replaceable></arg><arg choice="plain">&Dash;&Dash;deviceport <replaceable>
device_port</replaceable></arg><arg>&Dash;&Dash;sslproxyhost <replaceable>
proxy_host</replaceable></arg><arg>&Dash;&Dash;sslproxyport <replaceable>
proxy_port</replaceable></arg><arg><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;property (<replaceable>
name</replaceable>=<replaceable>value</replaceable>)[:<replaceable>name</replaceable>=<replaceable>
value</replaceable>]*</option></arg><arg choice="plain"><replaceable>load_balancer_name
</replaceable></arg>
</cmdsynopsis></refsynopsisdiv>
<refsect1><title>&desc-tt;</title>
<para>Use the <command>create-http-lb</command> command to create a physical
load balancer associated with a load balancer configuration. A physical load
balancer is a representation of the actual load balancer device defined by
its device host and port information. The physical load balancer enables you
to automatically apply changes made to the load balancer configuration without
running <command>export-http-lb-config</command> and manually copying the
generated load balancer configuration file to the web server instance. Set <literal>
autoapplyenabled</literal> to <literal>true</literal> to automatically apply
changes.</para>
</refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&opts-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="medium">&options-common;
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;config</option> </term>
<listitem><para>The name of the load balancer configuration referenced by
the load balancer being created.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;autoapplyenabled</option> 
</term><listitem><para>If set to <literal>true</literal>, <?Pub Caret>changes
to the load balancer configuration are automatically pushed to the physical
load balancer. If set to <literal>false</literal>, the changes won't be automatically
applied. Use the command apply-http-lb-changes to apply the changes manually.
The default is <literal>false</literal>.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;devicehost</option> 
</term><listitem><para>The device host or the IP address of the load balancing
device. This host or IP is where the physical load balancer will reside. 
</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;deviceport</option> 
</term><listitem><para>The port used to communicate with the load balancing
device. It must be SSL enabled.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;sslproxyhost</option> 
</term><listitem><para>The proxy host used for outbound HTTP.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;sslproxyport</option> 
</term><listitem><para>The proxy port used for outbound HTTP.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
<varlistentry><term><option role="nodash">&Dash;&Dash;property</option> </term>
<listitem><para>Optional attribute name/value pairs for configuring the load
balancer. </para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&oper-tt;</title>
<variablelist termlength="medium">
<varlistentry><term><replaceable>lb_name</replaceable></term><listitem><para>
The name of the new load balancer. This name must not conflict with any other
load balancers in the domain.</para>
</listitem></varlistentry>
</variablelist></refsect1>
<refsect1><title>&exam-tt;</title>
<example>
<title>Using the create-http-lb command</title>
<screen>asadmin> <userinput>create-http-lb --user admin --passwordfile password.txt 
--config mylbconfig --autoapplyenabled=true --devicehost host1 
--deviceport 5555 mylb

</userinput>
Command create-http-lb executed successfully.

</screen>
</example>
</refsect1>
